features.name: IMS,IMS_C,IMS_HHH Poorly processive, error-prone DNA polymerase involved in untargeted mutagenesis. Copies undamaged DNA at stalled replication forks, which arise in vivo from mismatched or misaligned primer ends. These misaligned primers can be extended by PolIV. Exhibits no 3'-5' exonuclease (proofreading) activity. May be involved in translesional synthesis, in conjunction with the beta clamp from PolIII
BPD_transp_1 ABC-type nitrate sulfonate bicarbonate transport system permease component
ABC_tran Part of the ABC transporter complex SsuABC involved in aliphatic sulfonates import. Responsible for energy coupling to the transport system
Bac_luciferase COG2141 Coenzyme F420-dependent N5,N10-methylene tetrahydromethanopterin reductase and related flavin-dependent oxidoreductases
Inhibitor_I9,Peptidase_S8 Belongs to the peptidase S8 family

Whib Acts as a transcriptional regulator. Probably redox- responsive. The apo- but not holo-form probably binds DNA

HTH_31,Pep_deformylase Removes the formyl group from the N-terminal Met of newly synthesized proteins. Requires at least a dipeptide for an efficient rate of reaction. N-terminal L-methionine is a prerequisite for activity but the enzyme has broad specificity at other positions

AAA_30,TrwC DNA-dependent ATPase and ATP-dependent 5'-3' DNA helicase. Has no activity on blunt DNA or DNA with 3'-overhangs, requires at least 10 bases of 5'-ssDNA for helicase activity
